1
00:00:01,520 --> 00:00:03,287
>> 在法国的一个偏远角落，
>> In a remote corner of France,

2
00:00:03,287 --> 00:00:07,760
一项堪称国家之最的基础设施工程正在如火如荼地推进。
work is underway on one of the country's most impressive infrastructure projects.

3
00:00:08,515 --> 00:00:12,440
>> >> 是一条路，但这可不是一条普通的路。
>> >> A road, but it's not just any old road.

4
00:00:12,440 --> 00:00:18,033
它拥有法国最长的大桥，沿途风景如画——但问题来了。
It contains France's longest bridge and most beautiful drives, but there's a problem.

5
00:00:18,033 --> 00:00:24,840
有一段还没修完，而且缺的还不是一点点，更要命的是，这个烂尾已经拖了很久很久。
There's a bit missing, quite a big bit in fact, and it's been missing for a very long time.

6
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:28,627
原因在于，走到今天这一步，远比想象中艰难。
That's because getting to this point has been far from easy.

7
00:00:28,627 --> 00:00:29,933
我们说的"偏远"，
When we say remote,

8
00:00:29,933 --> 00:00:34,400
可不是布列塔尼半岛的某个角落，也不是科西嘉岛的海岸线。
we don't mean a distant part of Brittany or the coast of Corsica.

9
00:00:35,120 --> 00:00:40,369
不，你得先抵达阳光明媚的地中海沿岸，
No, in fact, once you get to the sun-kissed shores of the Mediterranean,

10
00:00:40,369 --> 00:00:43,504
然后继续往前走，非常非常非常远——
keep going for a very, very, very long way,

11
00:00:43,505 --> 00:00:51,160
一直到印度洋，在距法国本土将近九千公里的地方，才能找到留尼旺岛（Reunion）。
here, to the Indian Ocean, where nearly 9,000 km from mainland France, you'll find the island of Reunion.

12
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:56,155
你可能在想：在这里建造大型基础设施工程，到底有多难？
Now, you might be thinking, how on Earth do you build a mega project here?

13
00:00:56,155 --> 00:00:57,495
这个问题问得好，
And it's a good question

14
00:00:57,495 --> 00:01:02,520
因为这里很可能是全球最难修一条路的地方之一。
because it may be one of the most difficult places in the world to build a road like this.

15
00:01:02,960 --> 00:01:08,317
这就是工程极限被不断突破的故事，
This is what happens when engineering is pushed to its absolute limits

16
00:01:08,317 --> 00:01:15,280
也是在地球上最孤立的角落之一建造超级工程所需要付出的一切。
and what it takes to build a mega builds in one of the most isolated corners of our planet.

17
00:01:17,720 --> 00:01:20,997
好，先上一堂简短的政治课。
Okay, let's start with a quick politics lesson.

18
00:01:20,997 --> 00:01:26,018
根据法兰西第五共和国宪法第一条，
According to Article 1 of the Constitution of the Fifth French Republic,

19
00:01:26,018 --> 00:01:33,200
法国是一个世俗、社会性且——对我们来说最重要的——不可分割的共和国。这究竟意味着什么？
France is a secular, social, and importantly for us, an indivisible republic, which means what exactly?

20
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:41,920
换句话说，法国就是法国，不管你身处哪里——这里、那里、还是这里、那里，甚至这里。
Well, in other words, France is France, regardless of whether you're here, here, here, here, or even here.

21
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:47,233
因此，尽管留尼旺岛离南极比离巴黎更近，
So, despite Reunion being closer to the South Pole than to Paris,

22
00:01:47,233 --> 00:01:52,640
它依然是欧盟不可分割的一部分，在法国议会中拥有完整的代表席位。
it's an integral part of the EU and enjoys full representation in the French Parliament.

23
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:54,672
那这和我们有什么关系呢？
So, why does that matter?

24
00:01:54,672 --> 00:01:57,680
其实说白了，关系不大，除了面子问题——
Well, it doesn't really, except for prestige,

25
00:01:57,880 --> 00:02:02,178
因为这意味着"新海岸公路"（La Nouvelle Route du Littoral）
because this means that La Nouvelle Route du Littoral, or New Coastal Road,

26
00:02:02,178 --> 00:02:07,565
不仅是印度洋在建的最令人叹为观止的基础设施工程之一，
isn't just one of the most impressive infrastructure projects being built in the Indian Ocean,

27
00:02:07,565 --> 00:02:09,800
也是整个法国规模最大的工程之一。
it's also one of the biggest in France.

28
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:12,686
那到底是一个什么样的工程？
Anyway, what's this all about?

29
00:02:12,686 --> 00:02:18,240
留尼旺岛固然美丽，但这座岛屿的内陆被巨型火山所主宰。
Well, as beautiful as Reunion is, the island is dominated by these vast volcanoes.

30
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:20,888
正因为内陆几乎无法穿越，
Because of this impossible interior,

31
00:02:20,888 --> 00:02:24,446
大多数城镇散落在岛屿边缘——
most towns and cities are dotted around the island's edge,

32
00:02:24,446 --> 00:02:32,360
比如这里，圣但尼（Saint-Denis），岛屿的首府；还有这里，勒波尔（Le Port），岛屿港口所在地。而要往返于两地之间，
like this one, Saint-Denis, the island's capital, or this one, Le Port, which contains the island's port. To get between the two,

33
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:36,481
只能走这条路——利托拉尔公路（Route du Littoral），就是那条老路。
you've got to use this, the Route du Littoral, the old one, that is.

34
00:02:36,481 --> 00:02:42,055
建于1959年，它紧贴着峭壁，从海岸线上方蜿蜒而过。
Built in 1959, it tightly hugs the sheer cliffs as it passes above the shoreline.

35
00:02:42,055 --> 00:02:47,360
每天约有八万辆车经过这条路，但问题来了。
About 80,000 vehicles use this road every day, but there's a problem.

36
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:51,153
猛烈的狂风、暴雨和海浪不断袭击这座岛屿。
Violent winds, rain, and waves battered the island.

37
00:02:51,153 --> 00:02:54,856
我们必须清除所有大面积的东西。
We have to clear away anything with a large surface area.

38
00:02:54,856 --> 00:02:57,520
这意味着阵风时速可达两百公里。
That means gusts of up to 200 km an hour.

39
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:03,334
这条路虽然至关重要，但开车走在上面，却像是夹在魔鬼与深蓝大海之间进退两难。
As vital as this road is, driving it is like being caught between the devil and the deep blue sea.

40
00:03:03,334 --> 00:03:06,186
这片海域的飓风十分频繁，
Cyclones in this part of the ocean are common,

41
00:03:06,186 --> 00:03:09,720
带来的巨浪和时速高达一百英里的狂风不断冲击着公路，
battering the road with waves and winds of up to 100 mph,

42
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:12,696
而受苦的不只是路面本身。
and it's not just the road that takes a beating.

43
00:03:12,696 --> 00:03:16,080
风化侵蚀不断啃噬着悬崖壁面，
The elements cause constant erosion to the cliff face,

44
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:20,843
将巨石碎块轰然砸向路面和过路的车辆行人。
sending rocks and boulders hurtling down onto the road and road users below.

45
00:03:20,843 --> 00:03:22,778
2006年3月24日，一整段悬崖突然崩塌，
On the 24th of March, 2006,

46
00:03:22,778 --> 00:03:30,520
大量岩石倾泻而下，造成两人罹难。
an entire section of the cliff gave way, sending tons of rock onto the highway below and killing two people.

47
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:38,720
这场悲剧发生后，一个更好的解决方案开始被提上日程。
After this tragedy, work began on a better solution.

48
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:43,664
第一项任务，是研究岩石从悬崖上滚落的最大距离，
The first job was to study the maximum distance rocks could fall from the cliff

49
00:03:43,664 --> 00:03:47,513
并以此划定安全边界——任何新路都必须建在这条线以外。
and to establish a perimeter that any new road would have to lay beyond.

50
00:03:47,513 --> 00:03:54,046
在此基础上，一个大胆的方案被提了出来：将新的海岸公路推向近海，建在安全水域之上。
From there, an ambitious solution was proposed, a new coastal road pushed safely offshore.

51
00:03:54,045 --> 00:03:58,041
第一段将建在高达17米的防波堤之上，
The first part would sit on top of a dyke up to 17 m high

52
00:03:58,041 --> 00:04:02,949
并覆盖护甲层，以抵御百年一遇的风暴。
and covered in armor to help it resist even a once-in-a-century storm.

53
00:04:02,949 --> 00:04:08,771
之后，路线将潜入悬崖内部，穿越一条隧道，最终抵达圣但尼。
From there, it would dive into the cliff face and make the final entrance to Saint-Denis through a tunnel.

54
00:04:08,772 --> 00:04:11,538
然而，计划很快就脱轨了。
But the plan quickly came off the rails.

55
00:04:11,537 --> 00:04:15,681
早期勘探发现，岩层不适合钻探——
Early tests found that the rock was unsuitable for drilling,

56
00:04:15,681 --> 00:04:22,103
这意味着即便隧道方案可行，施工难度也将极高，造价同样极为昂贵。
meaning that any tunnel, if it was even possible, would be extremely difficult and expensive.

57
00:04:22,184 --> 00:04:28,480
方案几经比较，终于在2011年敲定了最终设计。
A few different options were looked at, and then, in 2011, a final plan was put forward.

58
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:35,248
说真的，不管有没有路，我其实真的很喜欢留尼旺岛的生活方式。
You know what? Road or no road, I actually really quite like the look of life in Reunion.

59
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:42,284
不好意思，我平时不会这样——但我真的在想，能不能在那里建一栋梦想中的家园？那会是什么样子？
Sorry, I don't normally do this, but I'm just wondering if I could maybe even build my dream house there. What would that even look like?

60
00:04:42,284 --> 00:04:45,640
我的好伙伴Rayon Design可以帮我实现这个想象。
Well, I can find out thanks to my mates at Rayon Design.

61
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:47,983
如果你是室内设计师或建筑师，
If you're an interior designer or an architect,

62
00:04:47,983 --> 00:04:51,920
Rayon是一个新一代CAD平台，将彻底改变你的工作体验。
Rayon is a next-generation CAD platform that's going to make your life a dream.

63
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:54,501
它从早期概念到施工图纸，
It's built to streamline the entire design process

64
00:04:54,501 --> 00:04:59,178
将整个设计流程整合到同一个平台上，全程一站搞定。
from early concept development all the way through to construction documents, all in one place.

65
00:04:59,178 --> 00:05:03,083
与传统CAD工具不同，Rayon让你同时完成精准技术图纸、
Unlike CAD tools, Rayon lets you create precise technical drawings,

66
00:05:03,083 --> 00:05:06,639
精美客户演示与灵感板，
produce stylized client presentations and inspiration boards,

67
00:05:06,639 --> 00:05:10,661
以及实时同步、高效管理的采购计划。
and manage procurement schedules that stay live-synced and efficient.

68
00:05:10,661 --> 00:05:14,650
再也不用为了出一套图纸，同时开着五个不同的软件。
No more juggling five different programs just to produce a single drawing pack.

69
00:05:14,651 --> 00:05:16,982
它甚至还整合了AI。比如说，
It even incorporates AI. For example,

70
00:05:16,981 --> 00:05:21,213
如果你在超过一万个图块的库里找不到需要的CAD图块，
if you can't find the CAD block you need in its library of over 10,000 blocks,

71
00:05:21,213 --> 00:05:23,383
几秒钟内就能自己生成一个。
you can create your own in just seconds.

72
00:05:23,383 --> 00:05:26,003
同样的AI，还能把平面图或剖面图
That same AI can take a floor plan or section

73
00:05:26,003 --> 00:05:29,904
一键转换为3D轴测视图。
and transform it into a 3D axonometric view with just a few clicks.

74
00:05:29,904 --> 00:05:31,790
而且由于Rayon完全基于网页端，
And because Rayon is fully web-based,

75
00:05:31,790 --> 00:05:36,940
你的团队可以实时协作，共享单一数据源，彻底告别版本混乱。
your team can collaborate in real time with a single source of truth model with no version confusion.

76
00:05:36,940 --> 00:05:39,910
现在，趁我继续在留尼旺岛设计梦想家园，
Now, while I carry on designing my dream home in Reunion,

77
00:05:39,910 --> 00:05:43,140
你也点击下方链接，免费试用Rayon吧。
why don't you hit the link below and try Rayon for free today.

78
00:05:43,140 --> 00:05:48,600
好了，先让大家回到视频里来。还想再加几棵棕榈树。
Anyway, for now, I'm going to let you guys get back to the video. Want to add a few more palm trees.

79
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:52,373
西段同样会建在防波堤上，
The western section of the route would once again be built on a dyke,

80
00:05:52,373 --> 00:05:58,333
但不是钻进地下，而是耸立起这条路的标志性景观——大沙卢普高架桥（Grand Chaloupe Viaduct）。
but instead of disappearing underground, it would rise onto its defining feature, the Grand Chaloupe Viaduct.

81
00:05:58,413 --> 00:06:02,705
大桥全长5.4公里，最远伸入海面300米，
Stretching for 5.4 km and up to 300 m away from the shore,

82
00:06:02,705 --> 00:06:10,993
将成为这条12.5公里线路的核心，建成后也将跻身法国最长大桥之列。
it would form the centerpiece of the 12.5 km route and once complete, would become the longest bridge in France.

83
00:06:10,993 --> 00:06:14,160
好，听起来很厉害。但有一点——
Okay, sounds great. Just one thing.

84
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:17,520
让我们再仔细看看留尼旺岛。
Let's take another look at Reunion.

85
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:22,891
在法国最大规模基础设施工程之一的工地上施工已经够难了——
As if building one of France's largest infrastructure projects wasn't enough,

86
00:06:22,891 --> 00:06:30,328
偏偏最近的大陆还在1600公里以外，你该怎么办？那就只能自给自足。
how do you also do that when the nearest continental landmass is over 1,600 km away? Well, you've got to be pretty self-sufficient.

87
00:06:30,328 --> 00:06:32,440
来看看这座大桥。
Let's take a look at that bridge.

88
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:37,937
岛上新建了两座混凝土工厂，专门负责浇筑结构所需的巨型构件。
Two new concrete factories were created on the island to cast the enormous components for the structure.

89
00:06:37,937 --> 00:06:39,883
大桥采用箱梁设计，
The bridge is a box girder design,

90
00:06:39,883 --> 00:06:44,920
通过拼接一系列预制空心结构来形成桥面跨段。
meaning the spans are created by joining together a series of precast hollow structures.

91
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:50,739
这些箱体内部布有预应力钢缆，将各段紧紧挤压在一起。
Inside these boxes are prestressed steel cables, which squeeze the different sections together.

92
00:06:50,739 --> 00:06:52,755
整座桥由48根桥墩支撑，
All of that sits on 48 piers,

93
00:06:52,755 --> 00:06:58,316
每根桥墩都经过精心设计，以减小潮汐与涌浪对结构的阻力。
each carefully designed to minimize resistance to the tides and swells of water.

94
00:06:58,316 --> 00:07:04,320
桥墩在路线西端附近预制浇筑，每个结构由两个模块组成。
The piers were cast here, near the western tip of the road. Each structure is made of two blocks.

95
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:11,002
底部基础高15米，重达4500吨，基底宽23米；
The base, 15 m tall, weighing 4,500 tons and featuring a 23-m wide foundation.

96
00:07:11,002 --> 00:07:16,080
其上为墩帽，高度介于9至21米之间。
On top of that, the pier head, measuring between 9 and 21 m.

97
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:21,760
要将这些混凝土巨物运到施工现场，需要一件特殊的装备。
To transport these concrete giants to the work sites, a special piece of equipment was needed.

98
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:24,480
认识一下——祖里特（Zurit）。
Say hello to Zurit.

99
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:29,796
整个项目的其他物资都尽量就近取材，唯独这件例外。
While everything else for this project was sourced as close as possible, this was the exception.

100
00:07:29,796 --> 00:07:35,303
这艘专门制造的驳船来自波兰，大小相当于一个足球场，
Constructed in Poland, this specially designed barge is the size of a football pitch

101
00:07:35,303 --> 00:07:41,663
船上配备混凝土搅拌设备和一台能起吊巨型桥墩的门式起重机。
and contains a concrete mixing facility and gantry capable of lifting the enormous pier sections.

102
00:07:41,663 --> 00:07:44,519
基础构件一件一件地运出去。
One at a time, foundations are sailed out.

103
00:07:44,519 --> 00:07:51,728
就位之后，祖里特的机组人员——像八爪鱼一样——将八条钢腿插入海床，稳固船体。
Once in position, Zurit's crew, for octopus, plants eight steel legs into the seabed to provide stability.

104
00:07:51,728 --> 00:07:55,400
桥墩基础随后被精确放入指定位置。
The foundations are then precisely lowered into place.

105
00:07:55,440 --> 00:07:59,437
落入海床之后，液压千斤顶将结构顶起40厘米，
Once on the sea floor, jacks raise the structure up 40 cm,

106
00:07:59,437 --> 00:08:04,123
再向底板下方的袋体注入混凝土。
allowing concrete to be injected into sacks beneath the base plates.

107
00:08:04,123 --> 00:08:06,880
安装全部48根桥墩，整整耗时四年。
It took 4 years to install all 48 piers.

108
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:11,213
安装完毕后，架桥机登场，将箱梁逐一安装到位。
Once in place, a beam launcher was used to install the box girders.

109
00:08:11,213 --> 00:08:16,093
它站立在桥墩上，同时在两侧各放置一片梁段，保持平衡。
Standing on a pier, it picks up deck pieces and installs them either side on a pier,

110
00:08:16,093 --> 00:08:18,068
它站立在桥墩上，同时在两侧各放置一片梁段，保持平衡。
two at a time to maintain balance.

111
00:08:18,068 --> 00:08:20,555
完成两个跨段大约需要一个月，
It takes a month to complete two spans,

112
00:08:20,555 --> 00:08:25,402
之后架桥机移位至下一根桥墩，重复同样的流程。
after which the launcher relocates to the next pier and repeats the process.

113
00:08:25,402 --> 00:08:30,480
2017年，历经四年施工，大沙卢普高架桥正式竣工。
In 2017, after 4 years of work, the Grand Chaloupe Viaduct was complete.

114
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:35,408
不过，尽管大桥可能是整个项目技术最复杂的部分，
But although the bridge might have been the most technically complex part of the road,

115
00:08:35,408 --> 00:08:37,680
让工程陷入僵局的，却不是它。
that isn't what brought the project to a halt.

116
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:40,875
问题出在防波堤上。
That came about with the dyke.

117
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:46,061
这些结构设计精妙，是要将海浪的力量逐步消耗殆尽，
These structures were intricately designed to exhaust the power of the sea

118
00:08:46,061 --> 00:08:48,080
而不是硬碰硬地抵挡。
instead of trying to resist it.

119
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:52,203
防波堤的建造，先从海床堆砌填方形成堤芯，
Initially, they're created by building up an embankment from the seabed.

120
00:08:52,203 --> 00:08:55,925
再在外部构筑一套精密的护甲防护体系。
From there, they're protected by a sophisticated system of armor.

121
00:08:55,925 --> 00:08:57,299
原理其实很简单：
The principle is simple.

122
00:08:57,300 --> 00:09:01,709
最外层由巨型浇筑混凝土块——护坡混凝土块（Accropode）——组成，直接承受海浪的全部冲击力。
The outer layer is formed of huge cast concrete boulders known as Accropodes.

123
00:09:01,709 --> 00:09:04,428
它们是抵挡汹涌海浪的第一道防线。
They take the full force of ocean swells.

124
00:09:04,428 --> 00:09:08,686
之后，海水被迫穿越一层又一层越来越细密的岩石，
From there, water is forced through layers of smaller and smaller rocks,

125
00:09:08,686 --> 00:09:13,003
形成一道密度递增的迷宫，将波浪的能量层层消耗殆尽。
creating an increasingly dense maze, which zaps the energy from the wave.

126
00:09:13,003 --> 00:09:18,840
效果很好，就是有一个问题：需要大量的岩石。
It's effective, but there's just one thing. It needs a lot of rock.

127
00:09:18,880 --> 00:09:23,459
为了解决这个问题，项目方提出在两处新开采石场——
To solve that problem, the project owners proposed opening two new quarries,

128
00:09:23,459 --> 00:09:25,930
布兰白（Bois Blanc）和圣卢（Saint-Leu）。
here at Bois Blanc and here at Saint-Leu.

129
00:09:25,930 --> 00:09:28,353
这两处采石场本应绰绰有余，
These two sites would be more than enough

130
00:09:28,353 --> 00:09:33,258
足以提供完成防波堤所需的约700万立方米岩石。
to supply the estimated 7 million cubic meters of rock needed to complete the dyke.

131
00:09:33,258 --> 00:09:39,274
但麻烦就在这时来了。公众对采石场的强烈反对席卷而来。
But that's when they ran into trouble. Public backlash against the quarries was intense.

132
00:09:39,275 --> 00:09:44,339
这正是安东尼奥·卡代特（Antonio Cadet）和"别动我们的石头"社区团体所担忧的事。
It's what bothers Antonio Cadet and a community group called Don't Touch Our Rocks.

133
00:09:44,339 --> 00:09:49,280
他们认同修路的必要性，但坚决反对其中一个采石场选址。
They agree the road is necessary, but they're opposed to one of the quarry sites.

134
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:52,615
当地居民和环保团体纷纷表示反对，
Local residents and environmental groups opposed the plans,

135
00:09:52,615 --> 00:09:56,402
称爆破作业和重型卡车的频繁往来将严重干扰日常生活，
claiming blasting and heavy truck traffic would disrupt daily life,

136
00:09:56,402 --> 00:10:01,320
产生大量灰尘和噪音，并威胁到附近居民区和生态敏感地带。
generate dust and noise, and threaten sensitive ecosystems close to homes and habitats.

137
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:05,810
你看这里的风，尘土将会飘散到每一个角落，
With the wind you see here, we're going to have dust everywhere around,

138
00:10:05,810 --> 00:10:08,149
所有人都会受到影响，
and all the people are going to be concerned,

139
00:10:08,150 --> 00:10:11,944
尤其是孩子、老人，还有那些本就体弱多病的人。
especially the children and old people and people with already a disease.

140
00:10:11,984 --> 00:10:13,645
先停一下——
Now, before your very eyes,

141
00:10:13,645 --> 00:10:18,504
我们不能低估这个项目背后的环境隐忧。
it's important not to underestimate the environmental concerns of this project.

142
00:10:18,503 --> 00:10:22,440
留尼旺岛能成为令人心旷神怡的度假天堂，不是没有原因的。
Reunion isn't an idyllic island paradise for nothing.

143
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:26,779
岛屿周边海域孕育着珍贵的珊瑚礁、
The waters around Reunion are home to impeccable coral reefs,

144
00:10:26,779 --> 00:10:30,000
鲸鱼迁徙路线和海豚觅食场所。
whale migration routes, and dolphin feeding grounds.

145
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:36,088
在这一路段选用高架桥方案，部分原因正是为了尽量减少对自然环境的影响——
Part of the reason the bridge was chosen for this stretch of the route was to minimize the impact on nature,

146
00:10:36,088 --> 00:10:40,260
而对岛屿生态的担忧，并不止于水岸边缘。
and those concerns over the island's ecology don't stop at the water's edge.

147
00:10:40,260 --> 00:10:44,017
在这里开采一座采石场，将造成毁灭性的破坏。
The impacts of opening a quarry here would be devastating.

148
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,973
结果，在2018年，
And sure enough, in 2018,

149
00:10:45,973 --> 00:10:51,130
法院以"将破坏多种受保护物种的栖息地"
on the ground that it would destroy the habitats of several protected species,

150
00:10:51,129 --> 00:10:53,840
为由，裁定禁止新建任何采石场。
the court ruled against any new quarries.

151
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:56,680
这是一记毁灭性的打击，
It was a devastating blow,

152
00:10:57,040 --> 00:11:00,000
但故事还没有结束。
but it's not the end of the story.

153
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:03,023
那些巨型火山也不是一无是处——
Those giant volcanoes aren't good for nothing.

154
00:11:03,023 --> 00:11:06,966
它们同样源源不断地为岛上"提供"岩石。
They're also responsible for spraying the island with rocks.

155
00:11:06,966 --> 00:11:07,969
数量之多，
So much, in fact,

156
00:11:07,969 --> 00:11:10,684
以至于多年来，岛上农民
that for years it's been a problem for farmers

157
00:11:10,684 --> 00:11:13,399
一直被土地上遍布的玄武岩巨石所困扰。
whose land is littered with basaltic boulders.

158
00:11:13,399 --> 00:11:16,040
于是，一个妙招应运而生。
So, an ingenious solution was found.

159
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,644
全岛农民
Farmers across the island

160
00:11:25,644 --> 00:11:29,238
受到鼓励，将田间的巨石推到路边，
were encouraged to roll boulders off their land to the roadside,

161
00:11:29,238 --> 00:11:33,000
由专人运往施工现场。
where they were picked up and transported to the construction site.

162
00:11:48,520 --> 00:11:49,023
皆大欢喜——
Win-win.

163
00:11:49,023 --> 00:11:50,846
农民清理了田地，
Farmers cleared their fields,

164
00:11:50,845 --> 00:11:54,365
项目也收集到数百万吨岩石。
and millions of tons of rock was collected for the road.

165
00:11:54,405 --> 00:11:56,315
但这个方案再巧妙，
But as elegant as the solution was,

166
00:11:56,315 --> 00:12:00,080
终究无法满足防波堤护甲层所需的全部岩石用量，
it still couldn't provide all the rubble needed for the road's armor,

167
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:01,862
而且更糟糕的还在后头。
and there was worse to come.

168
00:12:01,862 --> 00:12:07,120
一项评估发现，所需岩石的数量此前被严重低估了。
In a review, it was discovered that the quantity of rock needed had been massively underestimated.

169
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:13,880
不是700万立方米，而是需要1200万立方米，才能完成防波堤的建设。
Rather than 7 million cubic meters, 12 million were needed to finish the dike.

170
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:18,326
就这样，到2019年，项目陷入全面停滞。
And with that, in 2019, the project ground to a halt.

171
00:12:18,326 --> 00:12:22,012
团队研究了从南非运石的方案，
The team looked into sourcing rock from South Africa,

172
00:12:22,012 --> 00:12:26,880
但将岩石横跨两千公里运到留尼旺岛，成本高得令人咋舌。
but the cost of shipping it over 2,000 km to Reunion was astronomical.

173
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:30,006
这个项目不仅拥有法国最长的大桥，
As well as France's longest bridge,

174
00:12:30,006 --> 00:12:34,060
还解锁了另一项记录——只不过这个记录并不光彩。
the project had also picked up another, less welcome, record.

175
00:12:34,060 --> 00:12:37,494
在仅完成12.4公里中的8公里之后，
With just eight out of 12.4 km constructed,

176
00:12:37,494 --> 00:12:41,807
造价已飙升至逾20亿美元，
the cost had skyrocketed to over 2 billion US dollars,

177
00:12:41,807 --> 00:12:46,200
跻身全球最贵公路之列。
making it one of the most expensive roads in the world.

178
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:48,818
这个天价造价说来讽刺——
That price tag is bitterly ironic

179
00:12:48,818 --> 00:12:50,958
因为当初在规划阶段，
because back in the planning stage,

180
00:12:50,957 --> 00:12:54,625
将整条线路建成高架桥的方案
the idea of a bridge spanning the entire length of the route

181
00:12:54,625 --> 00:12:57,560
曾被直接否决，理由正是造价太高。
was ruled out because it would be too expensive.

182
00:12:58,320 --> 00:13:05,892
更糟的是，2021年发现，近800块护坡混凝土块安装有误；
To make matters worse, in 2021, it was discovered nearly 800 accropodes were incorrectly installed.

183
00:13:05,892 --> 00:13:08,416
为了纠正这些问题，又不得不拆除
A further 2,500 had to be removed

184
00:13:08,417 --> 00:13:13,159
另外2500块重新定位，光这一项就耗费了2000万欧元。
to reposition the faulty blocks at a cost of 20 million euros.

185
00:13:13,839 --> 00:13:20,509
2022年，留尼旺省议会咬牙拍板，批准将剩余路段以高架桥方案完工，
In 2022, the Reunion Council decided to bite the bullet and approved completing the road as a viaduct,

186
00:13:20,509 --> 00:13:24,629
预计将再增加约7亿欧元的总造价。
potentially adding another 700 million euros to the final bill.

187
00:13:24,629 --> 00:13:27,114
但即便如此，新麻烦接踵而至。
But even that came with complications.

188
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:31,386
专用驳船"祖里特"在2020年
Zurite, the specialist barge, had been sailed back to Europe in 2020

189
00:13:31,386 --> 00:13:33,180
大桥竣工后已驶回欧洲。
after the bridge was complete.

190
00:13:33,180 --> 00:13:37,191
最后一段路的前期准备工作于2025年底启动，
Preliminary work on the final stretch began at the end of 2025,

191
00:13:37,191 --> 00:13:40,693
高架桥主体施工预计于2027年开工，
and construction of the viaduct is due to begin in 2027

192
00:13:40,693 --> 00:13:43,240
完工日期现已定于2030年。
with a completion date now set for 2030.

193
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:47,771
与此同时，新公路已完工的路段已投入使用——
In the meantime, the existing parts of the new road are now in use,

194
00:13:47,771 --> 00:13:51,639
只不过中间缺口那段，仍需绕回旧路行驶。
albeit with a detour back onto the old road for the missing stretch.

195
00:13:52,760 --> 00:13:55,656
尽管新海岸公路历经波折，
Despite the shortcomings of the new coastal road,

196
00:13:55,656 --> 00:13:59,320
这座岛屿的工程实力绝不应被低估。
this island's engineering prowess is not to be underestimated.

197
00:14:00,760 --> 00:14:01,439
几十年来，
For decades,

198
00:14:01,439 --> 00:14:06,022
这个法国的偏远角落，一直在比欧洲任何地方都更为恶劣的环境中，缔造一个又一个工程壮举。
this remote corner of France has been building extraordinary feats of engineering

199
00:14:06,022 --> 00:14:09,360
这个法国的偏远角落，一直在比欧洲任何地方都更为恶劣的环境中，缔造一个又一个工程壮举。
in an environment far more hostile than anywhere in Europe.

200
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:14,743
三盆地高架桥等工程已经证明，
Projects like the three basins viaduct have shown that this extraordinary island

201
00:14:14,743 --> 00:14:19,120
这座非凡的岛屿能够创造出不仅实用、更令人叹为观止的基础设施。
can create infrastructure that's not just practical, but also beautiful.

202
00:14:19,839 --> 00:14:24,120
但在这里，一旦出了问题，四顾茫然，无处可求援。
But out here, when things go wrong, there's nowhere to turn to.

203
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:27,522
在如此偏远的地方挑战超级工程，光有工程专业能力还不够—— >> >> 你还必须有那股不管多难都要成功的意志。
Attempting a mega build in such a remote location

204
00:14:27,522 --> 00:14:30,898
在如此偏远的地方挑战超级工程，光有工程专业能力还不够—— >> >> 你还必须有那股不管多难都要成功的意志。
is not just about having >> >> engineering expertise.

205
00:14:30,898 --> 00:14:35,166
在如此偏远的地方挑战超级工程，光有工程专业能力还不够—— >> >> 你还必须有那股不管多难都要成功的意志。
You've also got to have that drive to succeed against all the odds.

206
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:41,200
新海岸公路的故事，并不会抹去留尼旺岛的成就。
The story of the new coastal road doesn't detract from Reunion's record.

207
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:45,440
它只是说明，这一切成就有多么非凡。
It merely shows how extraordinary it is in the first place.

